    "The government's policies encourage the construction industry to seek more environmentally friendly and sustainable building materials.",
    "To facilitate the effective implementation of a circular economy within the construction industry, it is imperative to incorporate social and economic considerations into the research framework.",
    "Furthermore, developing circular value chains through stakeholder collaborative efforts is crucial (Hossain et al. 2020).",
    "Formulating policies and regulations can be a robust driver for increasing market demand for biomaterials, ultimately contributing to sustainable bio-economy development (Aguilar et al. 2019).",
    "Additionally, certain policies may restrict the utilization of traditional building materials, particularly those with high carbon emissions (Yang et al. 2023)."
